cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on trajectory replanning for quadrotors, which is a robotics application. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a real-time B-spline based kinodynamic search algorithm to generate dynamically feasible trajectories for quadrotors. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper mentions integrating the replanning system with a monocular vision-based quadrotor. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions using an elastic optimization approach as a post-optimization process, which involves solving a Quadratically Constrained Quadratic Programming (QCQP) problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages, but rather on the development of a replanning system for quadrotors.
